To work alone thou hast the right, but never to the fruits thereof. Be thou
neither actuated by the fruits of action, nor be thou attached to inaction.

0 Dhananjaya, abandoning attachment and regarding success and failure alike,
be steadfast in Yoga and perform thy duties. Even-mindedness is called Yoga
